 Google Keep Clone
A lightweight, feature-rich Google Keep clone built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This application mimics the core functionality of Google Keep, allowing users to create, edit, archive, and delete notes with a clean, responsive interface.

 Features
Create Notes - Click "Take a note" to create new notes with titles and content

Edit Notes - Click on any note to edit its content

Archive Notes - Archive notes to keep your workspace clean

Bin/Trash - Move notes to bin and restore or permanently delete them

Search Notes - Search through all your notes by title or content

View Toggle - Switch between grid and list view

Persistent Storage - Notes are saved automatically in your browser's localStorage

Responsive Design - Works seamlessly on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices

Sidebar Navigation - Switch between Notes, Archive, Bin, Reminders, and Edit Labels

 Demo
You can try the live demo by opening the index.html file in your browser.

Project Structure
text
google-keep-clone/
├── index.html          # Main HTML structure
├── style.css           # All styling and responsive design
├── script.js           # Application logic and functionality
└── assets/
    └── keep-icon.png   # Google Keep icon (add your own image)
🔧 Installation
Clone or download this repository

Add your Google Keep icon:

Place your Google Keep image (PNG, SVG, or JPG) in the assets/ folder

Name it keep-icon.png or update the path in index.html

Open index.html in your web browser

No build tools or dependencies required!

📖 How to Use
Creating a Note
Click the "Take a note" field in the composer

Enter a title and content

Click "Save" to add your note

Editing a Note
Click on any note card to open it in the modal

Make your changes and click "Save"

Archiving a Note
Hover over any note card

Click the archive icon (box with arrow)

Archived notes appear in the "Archive" section

Moving to Bin
Hover over any note

Click the bin icon to move it to trash

View all deleted notes in the "Bin" section

Restoring from Bin
Navigate to the "Bin" section

Click the restore icon on any note to recover it

Permanently Deleting
In the "Bin" section, click the delete forever icon

Confirm the action when prompted

Searching
Use the search bar at the top to find notes by title or content

Changing Views
Click the grid/list view toggle to switch between layouts

Customization
Changing the Icon
Replace assets/keep-icon.png with your own image file. Update the src attribute in both <img> tags in index.html:

html
<img src="./Assets/Google Keep icon.png" alt="Google Keep" width="32" height="32" />
Styling
Modify style.css to change colors, fonts, spacing, and overall appearance. Key variables include:

#1a73e8 - Primary blue color

#fbbc04 - Yellow Keep color

#f1f3f4 - Background gray

Data Storage
Notes are stored in the browser's localStorage under the key 'keep-clone-v1'. You can clear all notes by:

Opening browser dev tools (F12)

Going to Application → Storage → Local Storage

Deleting the keep-clone-v1 key

📱 Responsive Design
The application adapts to different screen sizes:

Desktop (1024px+): Full sidebar with labels

Tablet (820px-1024px): Collapsed sidebar with icons only

Mobile (600px): Horizontal sidebar, single column note grid

 Browser Support
Works in all modern browsers:

Chrome 60+

Firefox 60+

Safari 12+

Edge 79+

 Built With
